    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Phil</placeName>
                <date>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Septr 1850</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I presume that you have been already informed<lb/> that the cong at
                their late meeting came to no action in regard<lb/> to a Hazan. I understand that
                    <persName>Mr Hart</persName> intended calling a<lb/> special meeting on the
                subject.</p>
            <p>The bye law was rejected by a vote of 20 to 8. I will give you<lb/> the name (sub
                rosa) of those who voted in favour of it, for perhaps some<lb/> might not wish to be
                disgraced (!) by its being known that they were<lb/> in the minority. <persName>Mess
                    Wm. Florence</persName>, <persName>Mr Carffran</persName>, <persName>Mr
                    Nathans</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Mr D. Cohen</persName>, <persName>DHSolis</persName>, <persName
                    role="author">S. Solis</persName>, <persName>D. Pesoa</persName> and
                    <persName>Mr. Israel</persName> or <persName>Mr.<lb/> Lyons</persName> I do not
                recollect which. Some who I thought would have<lb/> voted for it, did not, so all
                hoped of its passing, is now at an end.<lb/> We shall expect you to stop and dine
                with us during the festivals<lb/> when not specially engaged.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">S Solis</persName>
            </p>
            <p>They have done me the honor of appointing me Hatan Torah in<lb/> conjunction with
                    <persName>Mr. Levi</persName> or <persName>Arnold</persName>.</p>
        </body>
